What are the doing, they keep giving the ball away as if they are playing Sunday League football, they are not trying hard enough as if Shrewsbury were never going to comeback and though Shrewsbury were some Non-League team. Fabinho, why you used to be so good now what. He needs to regain sharpness. Lovren what are you doing when you conceded he second goal. Minamino was underperforming like in the Everton game. Klopp should have a really big rant at the players at tell them off for heir carelessness today. Uhh another game when this team should have 2 weeks break. Klopp and Guardiola are right and wrong when they said scrapping replay. It is bad for big teams because of the congested games like Liverpool this season but good for the small teams as if they played at home like Shrewsbury today and they play at home to a big team, hey can go to their stadium and yeah. Or if the small team drew to a bigger team away. They can go back home telling they drew to a big team then they can have the Home advantage. Let that be a lesson learned. And can Klopp play more of the second team like Alex Ox and Adam the llama. Sorry I need something to cheer me up

snippet.textDisplay: As a Liverpool fan now living in the Midlands I loved this game, better than the Everton tie. Shrews had us in a right mess a few times with some great passing and to come back from that second half start is nothing but grit. Bit of a reality check for us and a welcome one at that, and how awesome that we get to watch a replay at anfield so some of the shrews players and staff (who supported Liverpool, I believe one was even in Istanbul) gets to experience a knockout game at anfield. Bring it on, I hope we get a good game, I'm a red through and through but we can't deny the FA cup is something special and way underated by bigger teams. If we aren't gonna win this cup because we are focusing on the league I want shrews to be the ones to take us out, hats off to them GG all :)
